  // 2017 PFO CLOSURE CLUSTER — CLOSE, RESPECT (long-term), REDUCE
  // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  // All three published NEJM 2017;377(11), September 14, 2017 issue.
  // Together they resolved a decade of pre-2017 PFO-closure ambiguity
  // (CLOSURE-I 2012 negative; original RESPECT 2013 borderline; PC 2013
  // negative) and now support AHA/ASA 2021 Class IIa, Level B-R for PFO
  // closure in non-lacunar stroke <60 with no other apparent etiology.
  // Atrial fibrillation excess is the central trade-off across all three.
  // listCategory: 'antiplatelets' — comparator arm is antiplatelet medical
  // therapy; no other valid listCategory key fits ('thrombolysis',
  // 'thrombectomy', 'carotid', 'acute' all wrong). Documented as a judgment
  // call in src/data/trialListData.ts and the evidence packets.
  // Evidence packets:
  //   docs/evidence-packets/close-2017-2026-05-20.md
